.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
Performs one of the following power actions on the specified instance:
.INDENT 0.0
.IP \(bu 2
\fBSTART\fP \- Powers on the instance.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBSTOP\fP \- Powers off the instance.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBRESET\fP \- Powers off the instance and then powers it back on.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBSOFTSTOP\fP \- Gracefully shuts down the instance by sending a shutdown command to the operating system. After waiting 15 minutes for the OS to shut down, the instance is powered off. If the applications that run on the instance take more than 15 minutes to shut down, they could be improperly stopped, resulting in data corruption. To avoid this, manually shut down the instance using the commands available in the OS before you softstop the instance.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBSOFTRESET\fP \- Gracefully reboots the instance by sending a shutdown command to the operating system. After waiting 15 minutes for the OS to shut down, the instance is powered off and then powered back on.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBSENDDIAGNOSTICINTERRUPT\fP \- For advanced users. \fBWarning: Sending a diagnostic interrupt to a live system can cause data corruption or system failure.\fP Sends a diagnostic interrupt that causes the instance\(aqs OS to crash and then reboot. Before you send a diagnostic interrupt, you must configure the instance to generate a crash dump file when it crashes. The crash dump captures information about the state of the OS at the time of the crash. After the OS restarts, you can analyze the crash dump to diagnose the issue. For more information, see \fI\%Sending a Diagnostic Interrupt\fP <\fBhttps://docs.cloud.oracle.com/iaas/Content/Compute/Tasks/sendingdiagnosticinterrupt.htm\fP>\&.
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
For more information about managing instance lifecycle states, see \fI\%Stopping and Starting an Instance\fP <\fBhttps://docs.cloud.oracle.com/iaas/Content/Compute/Tasks/restartinginstance.htm\fP>\&.
.UNINDENT
